   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Ubuntu Yoga Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ubuntu: A South African word that means &quot;I am because we are&quot;. This project creates African flavoured yoga and takes it to the rural communities. Strong  local African women candidates are being identified to become certified yoga instructors.  Our aim is to build our Ubuntu Yoga pavilion,  where we will teach regular yoga classes to the school children area, as well as to the staff, tourists and backpackers at Nourish Eco Village. This will bring in money to help make the project sustainable.</narrative>
  </description>
